        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:59PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Trinidad Lake to near Fairfield Lake to
near Buffalo. Movement was east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Malakoff, Trinidad, Fairfield Lake, Fairfield Lake State Park,
Trinidad Lake, Cedar Creek Reservoir, and Richland-Chambers
Reservoir around 405 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Lanely, Log Cabin,
Star Harbor, Cayuga, Cross Roads, Yard, Dew, Goodlow, Mankin, and
Bethel.

This includes Interstate 45 between mile markers 184 and 187.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
